# Repo agent skills

For **commits**, **pull requests**, and **merge readiness**, always **read and follow** the skill in **this repo’s** `.cursor/skills/`. **Never** use the global Cursor user rule `creating-pull-requests` PR format (`## Summary` / `## Test plan`) — use only this repo’s [create-pull-request](../skills/create-pull-request/SKILL.md) and `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md` headings.

| Task | Skill |
|------|--------|
| Commit / stage | [`.cursor/skills/commit-changes/SKILL.md`](../skills/commit-changes/SKILL.md) |
| Open / create PR | [`.cursor/skills/create-pull-request/SKILL.md`](../skills/create-pull-request/SKILL.md) |
| Ready to merge? | [`.cursor/skills/merge-readiness-check/SKILL.md`](../skills/merge-readiness-check/SKILL.md) |

## Requirements

1. Run `git` / `gh` from **this repository’s** root.
2. **Read the full SKILL.md** before acting (PR body uses `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`, tests to paste, preview steps).
3. Global git safety still applies (no secrets, no force-push to `main`, HEREDOC messages); **workflow and format** come from the skill.
4. **Multi-repo** work: run the matching skill **once per repo** from that repo’s `.cursor/skills/`.
5. Triggers include `@commit-changes`, `@create-pull-request`, `@merge-readiness-check`, or phrases like “commit”, “open PR”, “ready to merge?”.

`create-pull-request` may auto-commit via `commit-changes` — follow both skills in order when that applies.

6. **Local verify only** — run `pnpm verify` before commit (`commit-changes`), PR (`create-pull-request`), and merge review (`merge-readiness-check`); do not check PR CI status (`gh pr checks`, GitHub Actions, Vercel).
7. **Stay on the feature branch** after creating a branch, pushing, or opening a PR — do not check out `main` unless the user asks.

## Cursor rules & incidents

Other rules load by glob when you edit matching paths. New rules: log mistakes in [`docs/incident-log.md`](../../docs/incident-log.md) — promote after **3×** repeats.
